      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for constitutive model selection; sensitivity analysis on material model parameters completed.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V rod and screw modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening; UHMWPE vertebral body blocks modeled with Neo-Hookean hyperelastic constitutive law. Literature support provided for both selections. Parametric sensitivity on tangent modulus (±20%) showed <4% effect on yield force QoI, confirming model form adequacy for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified coupon testing of same material lot; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus and yield strength from tensile coupon testing of same material lot as test constructs (n=5 coupons, mean E=114 GPa). UHMWPE block properties from supplier certificate of conformance supplemented by literature. Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements of three representative specimens; nominal CAD dimensions confirmed within 0.05 mm."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs assembled from production-representative hardware; dimensional inspection performed on all specimens.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws and 5.5 mm titanium rods. All hardware from released production lots. Dimensional inspection confirmed all screws within drawing tolerances. Constructs assembled by trained technicians following clinical technique guide. Sample size exceeds minimum N=10 for this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate ASTM F1717 standard configuration; multiple test conditions assessed to bound COU.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed per ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol at a single load configuration (standard 5-hole construct, 40 mm offset). Only one test condition evaluated; multi-condition coverage not achieved. This factor is below required level, consistent with the COU description noting the single-condition limitation. Risk accepted given direct comparison to bench test data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading match experimental setup; torque application to set screws verified equivalent.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry including superior and inferior potting constraints. Crosshead displacement rate matched to quasi-static FEA assumption. Set screw torque preload applied in FEA via pretension elements calibrated to experimental torque values (4 Nm). Equivalency confirmed by overlay of initial linear stiffness response."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; percent difference < 10% for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness (FEA 287 N/mm vs. experimental mean 294 N/mm, 2.4% difference, E/uval 0.81), yield force (FEA 1842 N vs. experimental mean 1798 N, 2.4% difference, E/uval 1.12), force at 40 mm (FEA 2104 N vs. experimental mean 2031 N, 3.6% difference, E/uval 0.94). All acceptance criteria satisfied across N=11 constructs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to COU decision context; stiffness, yield force, and ultimate force are regulatory submission endpoints.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the ASTM F1717 standard and required for 510(k) submission. Each QoI maps directly to a clinical failure mode (construct loosening, permanent deformation, catastrophic failure). QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical affairs team."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
